==English==
===Etymology===
Latin ''[[tangibilis]]'', from ''[[tangere]]'', "to touch".

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

#touchable; able to be [[touch]]ed or [[feel|felt]]; [[perceptible]] by the [[sense of touch]]; [[palpable]]
#possible to be treated as fact; [[real]] or [[concrete]]
#[[comprehensible]] by the [[mind]]; [[understandable]]

====Translations====
*French: [[#French|tangible]]
*German: [[greifbar]] (1), [[erfühlbar]] (1), [[konkret]] (2), [[erfaßbar]] (3), [[faßbar]] (3), [[begreifbar]] (3)
*Ido: tushebla
*Portuguese: [[tangível]] (1,2)

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# real or concrete results
#:''Yes, but what are the tangibles?''

===Related terms===
*[[real]]
*[[palpable]]
*[[touch]]

